article.description: — Carter Collins had 22 points as Davidson defeated Rhode Island 67-58 on Friday night.
article.headline: Collins scores 22 to lift Davidson past Rhode Island 67-58
article.linkText: Collins scores 22 to lift Davidson past Rhode Island 67-58
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. -- — Carter Collins had 22 points as Davidson defeated Rhode Island 67-58 on Friday night. The game marked the first Atlantic 10 Conference matchup of the season for both teams. Hyunjung Lee had 16 points for Davidson (4-3). Kellan Grady added 11 points. Luka Brajkovic had 10 points. Malik Martin scored a career-high 20 points for the Rams (3-5). Makhel Mitchell added 12 points. Fatts Russell had six assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
